<collectingCountry box="[537,668,965,990]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">Cape Verde</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fransen" box="[684,842,966,990]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" refString="Fransen, C. H. J. M. (1990) Bitias stocki, a new genus and new species of pandalid shrimp (Crustacea, Decapoda, Caridea) in the eastern Atlantic Ocean. Beaufortia, 41, 67 - 73." type="journal article" year="1990">
Fransen 
<number box="[782,842,966,990]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The present specimens represent the first record of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,248,1001,1025]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Bitias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stocki">
<emphasis box="[151,248,1001,1025]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">B. stocki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[419,484,1002,1025]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Bitias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[419,484,1002,1025]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">Bitias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the western Atlantic (
<collectingCountry box="[797,871,1001,1026]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">Brazil</collectingCountry>
). The Brazilian material agrees well with the 
<typeStatus box="[1387,1436,1002,1026]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName box="[282,379,1037,1061]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Bitias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stocki">
<emphasis box="[282,379,1037,1061]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">B. stocki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as described and illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fransen" box="[739,913,1038,1062]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" refString="Fransen, C. H. J. M. (1990) Bitias stocki, a new genus and new species of pandalid shrimp (Crustacea, Decapoda, Caridea) in the eastern Atlantic Ocean. Beaufortia, 41, 67 - 73." type="journal article" year="1990">
Fransen (
<number box="[844,905,1038,1062]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" value="1990.0">1990</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The dorsal teeth on the carapace and rostrum are movable (posterior half of the rostrum and carapace posterior to the post-orbital margin) or fixed (distal half of the rostrum); their number ranges from 
<number box="[594,685,1109,1134]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" value="15.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="14.0">14 to 16</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[700,763,1109,1134]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1497,1519]" captionTargetBox="[152,1396,194,1496]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1502]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Bitias stocki Fransen, 1990: male from TAAF station 65, off Rio de Janeiro, Brazil (MZUSP 31150) (a – e); two females from TAAF station 43, off Espírito Santo, Brazil (MZUSP 31148, 31149) (f, g); holotype, male from the Azores (RMNH D 39051) (h); a, frontal region, dorsal; b, carapace with eyestalks, lateral; c, abdomen, lateral; d, telson, dorsal; e, uropod, dorsal; f, carapace with eyestalks, lateral; g, anterior portion of carapace with eyestalks, lateral; h, diagram of first to fifth abdominal sternites, ventral (based on drawing by C. H. J. M. Fransen)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231092/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">
Fig. 
<number box="[752,763,1109,1134]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
b, f, g). The ventral subdistal tooth may be present or absent and the development of the lateral rostral carina is also variable (
<figureCitation box="[877,940,1145,1170]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1497,1519]" captionTargetBox="[152,1396,194,1496]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1502]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Bitias stocki Fransen, 1990: male from TAAF station 65, off Rio de Janeiro, Brazil (MZUSP 31150) (a – e); two females from TAAF station 43, off Espírito Santo, Brazil (MZUSP 31148, 31149) (f, g); holotype, male from the Azores (RMNH D 39051) (h); a, frontal region, dorsal; b, carapace with eyestalks, lateral; c, abdomen, lateral; d, telson, dorsal; e, uropod, dorsal; f, carapace with eyestalks, lateral; g, anterior portion of carapace with eyestalks, lateral; h, diagram of first to fifth abdominal sternites, ventral (based on drawing by C. H. J. M. Fransen)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231092/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">
Fig. 
<number box="[929,940,1145,1170]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
b, f, g).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,533,1494]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">
An important morphological feature of 
<taxonomicName box="[641,737,1181,1205]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Bitias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stocki">
<emphasis box="[641,737,1181,1205]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">B. stocki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
not mentioned nor illustrated in the original description of the species (
<bibRefCitation author="Fransen" box="[246,400,1218,1242]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" refString="Fransen, C. H. J. M. (1990) Bitias stocki, a new genus and new species of pandalid shrimp (Crustacea, Decapoda, Caridea) in the eastern Atlantic Ocean. Beaufortia, 41, 67 - 73." type="journal article" year="1990">
Fransen 
<number box="[343,400,1218,1242]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) is the presence of sharp processes on the abdominal sternum. All three Brazilian specimens have a pair of spine-like processes on the first to fourth abdominal sternites, strongest on the first and diminishing in size towards the fourth; the fifth sternite has a small median process continued by a median carina. At our request, Dr. Charles H.J.M. Fransen examined the 
<typeStatus box="[723,821,1325,1350]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[860,957,1325,1349]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Bitias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stocki">
<emphasis box="[860,957,1325,1349]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">B. stocki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34992" box="[972,1058,1326,1350]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34992" name="National Museum of Natural History, Naturalis" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">RMNH</collectionCode>
<accessionNumber box="[1066,1168,1325,1350]" httpUri="http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/D39051" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">
D 
<number box="[1094,1168,1325,1350]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" value="39051.0">39051</number>
</accessionNumber>
), in which he found the same armature on the abdominal sternum. Dr. Fransen’s schematic drawing is reproduced here (
<figureCitation box="[1245,1310,1361,1386]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1497,1519]" captionTargetBox="[152,1396,194,1496]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1502]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Bitias stocki Fransen, 1990: male from TAAF station 65, off Rio de Janeiro, Brazil (MZUSP 31150) (a – e); two females from TAAF station 43, off Espírito Santo, Brazil (MZUSP 31148, 31149) (f, g); holotype, male from the Azores (RMNH D 39051) (h); a, frontal region, dorsal; b, carapace with eyestalks, lateral; c, abdomen, lateral; d, telson, dorsal; e, uropod, dorsal; f, carapace with eyestalks, lateral; g, anterior portion of carapace with eyestalks, lateral; h, diagram of first to fifth abdominal sternites, ventral (based on drawing by C. H. J. M. Fransen)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/231092/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">
Fig. 
<number box="[1299,1310,1361,1386]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
h), thereby completing the description of the 
<typeStatus box="[546,648,1397,1422]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">holotype</typeStatus>
. The only other presently known species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1170,1235,1398,1421]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Bitias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1170,1235,1398,1421]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">Bitias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the Indo-West Pacific 
<taxonomicName authority="Rathbun, 1906" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1906" box="[237,576,1433,1458]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Bitias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis box="[237,380,1433,1457]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">Bitias brevis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rathbun" box="[396,568,1433,1458]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" refString="Rathbun, M. J. (1906) The Brachyura and Macrura of the Hawaiian Islands. Bulletin of the United States Fish Commission, 23, 827 - 930, pls. 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1906">
Rathbun, 
<number box="[508,568,1433,1458]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" value="1906.0">1906</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, which differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[812,910,1433,1457]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pandalidae" genus="Bitias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stocki">
<emphasis box="[812,910,1433,1457]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="264">B. stocki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in only a few very subtle details (
<bibRefCitation author="Crosnier" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" refString="Crosnier, A. &amp; Fransen, C. H. J. M. (1994) Decouverte de Bitias brevis (Rathbun, 1906) a Madagascar (Decapoda, Pandalidae). Crustaceana, 66, 45 - 52. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1163 / 156854094 x 00143" type="journal article" year="1994">
Crosnier &amp; Fransen 
<number box="[246,306,1470,1494]" pageId="1" pageNumber="264" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
